text.value:
 To center the page content horizontally and vertically, you can make the following changes:

1. Add `display: flex` and `align-items: center` to the outer `div` to center it vertically:

```jsx
return (
  <div style={{ height: '100vh', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
    {/* page content */}
  </div> 
);
```

2. Wrap the rectangles in another `div` and add `margin: 0 auto` to center that div horizontally:

```jsx
return (
  <div style={{ height: '100vh', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
    <div style={{ margin: '0 auto' }}>
      {rectangles.map((rect, index) => (
        <Rectangle key={index} {...rect}/>  
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
);
```

So the full page component would be:

```jsx
const Home = () => {

  // rest of component

  return (
    <div style={{ height: '100vh', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
      <div style={{ margin: '0 auto' }}>
        {rectangles.map((rect, index) => (
          <Rectangle key={index} {...rect}/>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

This centers the page content vertically and horizontally on the screen.
